c.  Public Sector Job Evaluation/Remuneration Specialist  
(3 person-months, intermittent) 

9.  The public sector job evaluation/remuneration specialist will assist the Government in (i) 
designing and implementing a job evaluation, and (ii) establishing a merit-based remuneration 
policy with appropriate incentives and pay scales. The specific duties of the specialist include 
the following: 

(i)  assist in selecting an appropriate job evaluation model;  
(ii)  train  job  evaluators  in  ministries  and  central  agencies,  and  conduct  trial 
evaluations;  
(iii)  assess the validity of the trial evaluations and prepare an implementation plan; 
(iv)  advise the evaluation team on  job classification and grade structure formulation; 
(v)  review the proposed job grading and classifications to ensure consistency; 
(vi)  assist in the development of appropriate salary scales for job grades; 
(vii)  assist in drafting a merit-based pay policy with appropriate incentives;  
(viii)  assess the cost of implementation;  
(ix)  prepare (a) an interim progress report upon completion of the first part of the 
assignment,  and  (b)  a    final  report  of  findings  and  recommendations  upon 
completion of the second phase of the assignment; and  
(x)  undertake other duties and responsibilities as may be reasonably requested by 
ADB and the team leader.  

10.  The public job evaluation/remuneration specialist must have (i) in-depth knowledge and 
experience  in  public  sector  job  evaluation  and  performance-based  remuneration  policy 
development; (ii) extensive working experience in developing countries, preferably in the Pacific; 
and (iii) ability to work effectively in teams, and excellent communication skills. 

d.  Strategic Planning/Performance Management Specialist   
(4 person-months, intermittent) 

11.  The strategic planning/performance management specialist will strengthen the strategic 
and annual planning capacities of ministries and department. Specifically, the specialist will 

(i)  identify departments requiring assistance to strengthen their  internal planning 
and/or performance management capabilities; 
(ii)  develop a  model strategic plan and a planning guide with a glossary of standard 
terms  for departmental use;  
(iii)  prepare  a  prioritized  implementation  schedule  to  strengthen  the  planning 
capability of departments; 
(iv)  facilitate the preparation process of departmental  strategic and annual plans;  
(v)  develop a  model performance report for departments; 
(vi)  design public service  performance management and reporting procedures; 
(vii)  develop an action plan for assistance to departments in the preparation of their 
annual performance reports;  
(viii)  design an appropriate model  performance agreement for senior public service 
officers; 
(ix)  facilitate meetings with ministers, heads of departments, and senior officers to 
ensure that the concept of a performance agreement is understood and widely 
accepted;
